{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"2b8acd43-1bb6-4173-942d-2eac8edeedc7","content":"To switch from VSTest to Microsoft.Testing.Platform with MSTest.Sdk/3.8.0, you need to make these changes in your project file:\n\n1. **Remove** (or set to `false`) the VSTest opt-in:\n   ```xml\n   <!-- Delete this line -->\n   <UseVSTest>true</UseVSTest>\n   ```\n   Microsoft.Testing.Platform is the **default** runner in MSTest.Sdk 3.8+, so removing `UseVSTest` is all that's needed to enable it.\n\n2. **Run tests** with:\n   ```shell\n   dotnet test\n   ```\n   or directly execute the test binary (`./YourTests.exe`), which is a standalone test host under the new platform.\n\n### Other things to check\n\n- **`runsettings` files** — most VSTest `.runsettings` options still work, but custom adapters/extensions may need updates.\n- **CI scripts** — if you parse TRX output, it's still produced. If you use `vstest.console.exe` directly, switch to `dotnet test` or the native executable.\n- **Custom extensions** — VSTest adapters don't carry over; look for Microsoft.Testing.Platform equivalents.\n\nThat single property removal is the core change. Build & run your tests afterward to catch any incompatibilities.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"3638cc2f-904c-4b50-88e5-9800c546df51","outputTokens":313,"requestId":"4C26:1ED211:D63B01:10A668A:6A0129BD"},"id":"07b58016-38bf-46af-880a-2d85c960a054","timestamp":"2026-05-11T00:58:45.961Z","parentId":"c6721ea2-e95e-47cc-afe5-99ebaf4c0a16"}
